      "writtenOn": "2021-06-07T17:57:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Does this mean MSAA proxies weren\u0027t actually making copies like we thought they were?\n\nWill this change soon since we don\u0027t actually need a barrier in the MSAA, non-render-to-texture case?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 4523,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 4523,
        "endChar": 29
      },
      "revId": "ee96c1faa4345faa91300ad6f9136413889b7aef",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3c13ecf7_2fecfbf5",
        "filename": "src/gpu/gl/GrGLCaps.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 4523,
      "author": {
        "id": 5036
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-06-07T18:27:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I guess they weren\u0027t making copies if we had texture barrier support and the MSAA was a texture (i.e. had a resolve target). But I also feel like the barrier isn\u0027t doing anything here. Because if our code says to sample the RT in a shader we are going to use its resolve attachment as the texture. I\u0027m less familiar about how our code handles triggering resolves, but will an attempted resolve happen on each texture we sample in a draw? So thus a resolve is actually happening in msaa before each draw that needs to sample itself?",
      "parentUuid": "6c82196a_ff2bd392",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 4523,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 4523,
        "endChar": 29
      },
      "revId": "ee96c1faa4345faa91300ad6f9136413889b7aef",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d1555555_774ac663",
        "filename": "src/gpu/gl/GrGLCaps.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 4523,
      "author": {
        "id": 5085
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-06-07T18:56:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I thought we did insert resolves automatically based on sampling of textures, but wouldn\u0027t we need to break the render pass to make this actually resolve at the right time? I\u0027m not familiar enough with how this all works to know if it\u0027ll work out correctly.",
      "parentUuid": "3c13ecf7_2fecfbf5",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 4523,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 4523,
        "endChar": 29
      },
      "revId": "ee96c1faa4345faa91300ad6f9136413889b7aef",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2a11e9f2_93385ddc",
        "filename": "src/gpu/gl/GrGLCaps.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 4523,
      "author": {
        "id": 5633
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-06-07T19:26:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It must have been working correctly all along.\n\nIt is my understanding that the drawing manager does insert texture resolve tasks as needed, appropriately sets up dependencies, and splits up render passes. This ought to keep working if we don\u0027t insert barriers in cases were proxy-\u003erequiresManualMSAAResolve() is true. We also ought to do self reads in those cases even if there is no texture barrier support.\n\nThis CL doesn\u0027t seem to change any of the old functionality though. Should we land as-is and then fix up the MSAA self reads?",
      "parentUuid": "d1555555_774ac663",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 4523,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 4523,
        "endChar": 29
      },
      "revId": "ee96c1faa4345faa91300ad6f9136413889b7aef",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4ff0f56f_f8a4b4dd",
        "filename": "src/gpu/gl/GrGLCaps.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 4523,
      "author": {
        "id": 5036
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-06-07T19:53:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Wait we are doing copies still. We only get into this GL virtual if up in the GrCaps base class we can in this if:\n\nif (this-\u003etextureBarrierSupport() \u0026\u0026 !rt-\u003erequiresManualMSAAResolve()) {\n    return this-\u003eonGetDstSampleFlagsForProxy(rt);\n}\n\nIf we require manual resolves we always end up doing a copy.\n\nSo yeah this CL doesn\u0027t change how things work, and things work how we thought they did. In the future in setupDstProxy if this returns no sample flags, we can check if the RT is multisampled with a resolve and needing manual resolves. If so we can just trigger a resolve and set the dst proxy to the resolve without doing the full copy.\n\nThus if other things all area fine in this CL I say we land this as is.",
      "parentUuid": "2a11e9f2_93385ddc",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 4523,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 4523,
        "endChar": 29
